         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Bah, i don't want to argue with "they get that and not us". But in RP evolution i think this is totaly impossible. Explain me How an Hybrid class can develop spell with less resist, less cast time,than parent version. May be Parent class are too dumb to think about "hey, i'm weak in melee situation, so i need spell with better chance to land and more fast to cast".<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>I always felt that hybrids should sacrifice efficiency for cast time; without the cast time assistance, we might as well not have spells. However, giving us certain spells with a faster cast-time unbalances the spell and robs necromancers, I agree..the resistance thing completely baffles me. </P><P>I'm glad not everyone's panicking over Invoke Death and Lich, by the way. Thanks. We're on the same team, kids..</P><P>Hybrids have to have offshoots of spells as well because they don't always scale properly. It's like, "what's between Vampiric Curse and Bond of Death"? Nothing. Yet for SK's, Vampiric is ineffective while BoD would be potentially too powerful at that level when coupled with SK melee damage. Offshoots, and more melee-specific spells like Life Leech (as an Erudite, it's 20% of my mana..imagine some of the other SKs, lol) as a quick DPS boost that we can't maintain. When it comes to damage output over 2 minutes, there's very little difference. When it comes to damage output over 10 minutes..necros win. </P><P>Life Leech is an offshoot rather than an upgrade to the lifetap spells. It's even more mana-inefficient than the other taps. That's the kind of spell I like, though...it fits SK without robbing from necro. When it comes to pure, unadulterated improvements of the spell lines we share, then the parent class should be pioneering them, not the child class.</P><P></P><P></P><P></P><P><i