         I guess Lejina beat me to it on the reply, but oh well.  The three spells I saw you guys mention as having a problem with SK's recieving were Lich, Invoke Death, and Conjure Corpse, going through these spells:</P><P>Lich - SK's have many necromancer spells, all of these spells given to us at level 51 and later were designed entirely for Necros, however the play styles between SK's and Necros are entirely different, while a Necro sits down in the camp regaining mana an SK is standing up either hitting a mob or looking for a mob to hit, out of all the hybrids SK's use the most mana and med the least, that is why we asked for lich, right now SK's are basically extremly crippled in groups when a mana regen buff is not aviable for them, some SK's myself included can and do avoid this with a Soul Defiler (procs CoB) or Deathly Temptation (12 hp for 6 mana), this number is a rather small percentage of SK's however, lich will allow us to use our casting side enough to not rely on a group having an Enchanter, Bard, Beastlord, or Druid just so we can do what were supposed to do... melee and cast, also as was mentioned earlier, you guys have three or four upgrades to lich before we even get it, I really dont think this is a problem for you... 210 mana/minute for a SK (no ft/mc) compared to 640 mana/minute for a necro (no ft/mc) thats less than 1/3 of your mana regeneration.</P><P>Invoke Death: This is your level 49 pet, we get this at level 64, as a natural progression of our pets... the playstyle between Necros and SK's is very different so I probally look at this different than you, to me gebeker is my most efficent dot, and I would like an improvement to it, to you hes a shield, remember at 64 you have 4 pets which are better than this,  no one presented a good argument for why we shouldnt have this other than the usual "I dont like the idea of class x getting a spell I havent even memmed for 10 levels" that all hybrids have had to listen to since Kunark.  SK's getting this impacts Necros in no way at all, however it impacts me since its an improvement to my only DoT that is worth using for its damage feature.</P><P>Conjure Corpse: This was brought up a couple times, lets be honest here corpse summoning isnt fun, its expensive, you get jipped on being reimbursed coffins, forces you to use up inventory slots on coffins, and costs a ton of mana... of course for a necro you have that nifty robe... summon one corpse every 30 seconds with it, and by level 65 (when we get conjure corpse) mana regen rates and aa would let you do one every 15-20 seconds without a robe, for an sk its going to be more like one every 30-45 seconds (thats assuming i have a mage/cleric on me full time giving me mod rods).  To be honest with you guys I and many other SK's would trade our corpse summoning ability for the self only aa summon corpse.  One last point on this spell, this is the ONLY level 51+ necro spell SK's get with pop, take a look at what paladins and rangers take from clerics/druids, instead of complaining if I were you guys I would be extremly happy I dont have to share spells as much as those two classes do.</P><P>Brael Expleech<BR>60 SK Enlightened Dark<BR>Tarew Marr<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
